21:10.904 --> 21:12.639
[instrumental music]

21:18.645 --> 21:22.649
So, you had the opportunity
of a lifetime

21:22.683 --> 21:25.018
and you shot your boss.

21:25.051 --> 21:27.287
Good career move, Appleton.

21:28.955 --> 21:30.824
I would’ve been
at "The Chronicle"

21:30.857 --> 21:33.894
three years next month.

21:33.927 --> 21:35.896
This is the saddest day
of my life.

21:37.531 --> 21:39.766
I’m really gonna miss you.

21:39.800 --> 21:41.768
Are you gonna take
this stapler?

21:43.770 --> 21:46.540
‐You can have it.
‐Alright, thanks.

21:46.573 --> 21:49.876
I’m gonna turn around now,
Appleton. Don’t shoot.

21:49.910 --> 21:50.911
[laughs]

22:02.055 --> 22:04.991
Appleton, I’ve reconsidered.

22:05.025 --> 22:06.359
You’re not fired.

22:06.392 --> 22:07.828
Thank you, sir.
Thank you, sir.

22:07.861 --> 22:10.697
I‐I knew you’d realize that
I was a valuable employee

22:10.731 --> 22:13.466
and‐and that I‐I make a valuable
contribution to "The Chronicle"

22:13.499 --> 22:16.069
and‐and I knew you’d find it in
your heart to forgive me, sir.

22:16.102 --> 22:18.805
I’m not firing you
because the union won’t let me.

22:20.874 --> 22:22.809
That’s good enough for me, sir.

22:23.810 --> 22:25.779
Balki. Balki. Balki, good news.

22:25.812 --> 22:27.648
Wainwright was just here,
and‐and he left

22:27.681 --> 22:29.382
and‐and he said
he’s not gonna fire me.

22:30.416 --> 22:31.718
Well, that was quick.

22:31.752 --> 22:35.055
I just left a peace offering on
his desk not three minutes ago.

22:35.088 --> 22:36.456
What did you leave on his desk?

22:36.489 --> 22:38.091
A nice dish of three
larvae salad

22:38.124 --> 22:40.093
with a note saying
it was from you.

22:42.095 --> 22:44.030
Oh, my lord!

22:44.831 --> 22:47.100
[instrumental music]

22:55.041 --> 22:57.477
